    "searchText": "Zinc Zinc Citrate Zinc Gluconate Zinc (Form: as Zinc Citrate, and Zinc Gluconate) Fructose Sorbitol Honey powder Stearic Acid Citric Acid Natural Flavors Silica Vegetable Magnesium Stearate ITEM #4160 B41492 07D ACTUAL SIZE Dietary Supplement VEGETARIAN FORMULA\nGUARANTEED QUALITY\nLABORATORY TESTED No Gluten, No Yeast, No Wheat, No Milk or Milk Derivatives, No Lactose, No Soy, No Egg, No Grapefruit, No Fish, No Artificial Color, No Artificial Flavor, No Sodium. Directions: For adults and children 12 and over, dissolve one (1) lozenge in the mouth one or two times daily. Do not exceed two (2) per day. Limit use to no more than seven days. Zinc lozenges coat the membranes of your mouth and throat with zinc, providing a soothing effect.They have a delicious citrus flavor, and leave no objectionable aftertaste as some other lozenges do. WARNING: If you are pregnant, nursing or taking any medications, consult your doctor before use. Discontinue use and consult your doctor if any adverse reactions occur. Keep out of reach of children. Store in a cool, dry place. Do not use if seal under cap is broken or missing. (C) 2009 Good 'N Natural (R)"
